<main>

<div class="part"><span>Day 3 · Array Traversal</span></div>

<!-- 3.1 PRODUCT OF n-1 -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">3·1</span> Product of n−1 elements</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Given an array of n integers, print the resultant array with the product of n−1 elements.</div>

    <h3>Slide 1 — Question</h3>
    <p><span class="arr">[3,5,2,1,4]</span> → <span class="arr">[40,24,60,120,30]</span></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Index 0: exclude 3 → 5×2×1×4 = <b>40</b></li>
      <li>Verify last: exclude 4 → 3×5×2×1 = <b>30</b> <span class="ok">✓</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Slide 2 — Logic</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Same-size empty <code class="i">res</code> appears.</li>
      <li>Each cell is missing one number → add it back → every row = <b>120</b> = product of all.</li>
      <li>STEP 1: product = 120. STEP 2: <code class="i">res[i] = product / ar[i]</code> (strike-out cancels).</li>
      <li><code class="i">for(i=0;i&lt;5;i++) res[i]=product/ar[i]</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Return-array beat</h3>
    <p>1D <code class="i">int[]</code> · 2D <code class="i">int[][]</code> · float <code class="i">float[]</code> · boolean <code class="i">boolean[]</code>. <span style="color:var(--muted)">(Screenshot moment.)</span></p>

    <h3>Zero edge case (student input)</h3>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Input with 0 → <code class="i">ArithmeticException: / by zero</code></li>
      <li>Fix 1: <code class="i">if(ar[i]!=0)</code> around product → still crashes</li>
      <li>Fix 2: <code class="i">if(ar[i]!=0)</code> around division → works <span class="ok">✓</span></li>
    </ol>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>ProductArray.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">ProductArray</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[] <span class="nm">productArray</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> p = <span class="st">1</span>;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] != <span class="st">0</span>)
            {
                p = p * ar[i];
            }
        }

        <span class="ty">int</span>[] res = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[ar.length];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] != <span class="st">0</span>)
            {
                res[i] = p / ar[i];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">return</span> res;
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        <span class="ty">int</span>[] res = productArray(ar);

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; res.length; i++)
        {
            System.out.print(res[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
        }
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="run">
      <div class="rbar">▶ Run · ProductArray</div>
      <div class="rbody">
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">5</div><div class="in">4 3 1 2 5</div><div class="out">30 40 120 60 24</div></div>
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">5</div><div class="in">3 5 0 1 4</div><div class="out bad">ArithmeticException: / by zero<span class="cmt">   // before the guards</span></div></div>
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">5</div><div class="in">3 5 0 1 4</div><div class="out">20 12 0 60 15<span class="cmt">   // after both if(ar[i]!=0) guards</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- 3.2 SECOND LARGEST -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">3·2</span> Second largest — no sorting</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Given an array of n integers, print the second largest. <b>No sorting.</b></div>

    <h3>Slide — President / VP</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Start: P = MIN, VP = MIN. Example <span class="arr">[3,5,4,7,6,9,8]</span> → 8.</li>
      <li>3 → P=3 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 5 → demote: VP=3, P=5 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 4 → VP=4 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 7 → VP=5, P=7</li>
      <li><code class="i">if(ar[i]&gt;p){ vp=p; p=ar[i]; } else if(ar[i]&gt;vp) vp=ar[i];</code></li>
      <li>Largest → P, second → VP. O(n).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Fix 1 — negatives</h3>
    <p>Start both at <code class="i">Integer.MIN_VALUE</code> (0 fails for all-negative arrays).</p>

    <h3>Fix 2 — duplicate largest (interview)</h3>
    <p><code class="i">2 8 3 4 8 6 1</code> gives 8, but if 8 is the first largest you want <b>6</b>. Add <code class="i">&amp;&amp; ar[i]!=p</code>. Drop it if duplicates should count.</p>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>SecondLargest.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">SecondLargest</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static</span> <span class="ty">int</span> <span class="nm">secondLargest</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> p = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MIN_VALUE;
        <span class="ty">int</span> vp = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MIN_VALUE;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] &gt; p)
            {
                vp = p;
                p = ar[i];
            }
            <span class="kw">else if</span> (ar[i] &gt; vp &amp;&amp; ar[i] != p)   <span class="cm">// drop "&& ar[i]!=p" if duplicates allowed</span>
            {
                vp = ar[i];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">return</span> vp;
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        System.out.print(secondLargest(ar));
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="run">
      <div class="rbar">▶ Run · SecondLargest</div>
      <div class="rbody">
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">7</div><div class="in">2 8 4 9 6 3 10</div><div class="out">9<span class="cmt">   // 10 is first largest</span></div></div>
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">5</div><div class="in">-2 4 -6 7 8</div><div class="out">7<span class="cmt">   // negatives handled</span></div></div>
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">7</div><div class="in">2 8 3 4 8 6 1</div><div class="out">6<span class="cmt">   // distinct 2nd largest (with != p)</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<div class="part"><span>Day 4 · Array Pairs — Part A · Pair reductions</span></div>

<!-- P1 MAX PAIR SUM -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">4·1</span> Max pair sum</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Find the pair with the maximum sum. <b>No need to check all pairs</b> — max sum = largest + second largest.</div>

    <h3>Idea</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Reuse yesterday's second-largest code. Rename <code class="i">P → largest</code>, <code class="i">VP → secondLargest</code>.</li>
      <li><b>Drop</b> the <code class="i">&amp;&amp; ar[i]!=p</code> condition from yesterday — pairs must count duplicates.</li>
      <li>Return <code class="i">largest + secondLargest</code>.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>MaxPairSum.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">MaxPairSum</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static</span> <span class="ty">int</span> <span class="nm">maxPairSum</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> largest = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MIN_VALUE;
        <span class="ty">int</span> secondLargest = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MIN_VALUE;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] &gt; largest)
            {
                secondLargest = largest;
                largest = ar[i];
            }
            <span class="kw">else if</span> (ar[i] &gt; secondLargest)
            {
                secondLargest = ar[i];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">return</span> largest + secondLargest;
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        System.out.print(maxPairSum(ar));
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="run">
      <div class="rbar">▶ Run · MaxPairSum</div>
      <div class="rbody">
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">5</div><div class="in">8 9 4 6 7</div><div class="out">17<span class="cmt">   // 8 + 9</span></div></div>
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">7</div><div class="in">1 6 9 4 7 3 5</div><div class="out">16<span class="cmt">   // 9 + 7</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>


  </div>
</section>

<!-- P2 MIN PAIR SUM -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">4·2</span> Min pair sum</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Find the pair with the minimum sum = smallest + second smallest.</div>

    <h3>Changes from P1</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code class="i">largest → smallest</code>, <code class="i">secondLargest → secondSmallest</code></li>
      <li>Flip <code class="i">&gt;</code> to <code class="i">&lt;</code> · <code class="i">MIN_VALUE → MAX_VALUE</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Bug &amp; fix (student input)</h3>
    <p><code class="i">8 2 1 1 1</code> should give <b>2</b> (1+1) but gives <span class="bad">3</span> — the leftover <code class="i">!= smallest</code> condition blocked the duplicate. <b>Remove it</b> → <b>2</b> <span class="ok">✓</span></p>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>MinPairSum.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">MinPairSum</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static</span> <span class="ty">int</span> <span class="nm">minPairSum</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> smallest = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MAX_VALUE;
        <span class="ty">int</span> secondSmallest = <span class="ty">Integer</span>.MAX_VALUE;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] &lt; smallest)
            {
                secondSmallest = smallest;
                smallest = ar[i];
            }
            <span class="kw">else if</span> (ar[i] &lt; secondSmallest)
            {
                secondSmallest = ar[i];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">return</span> smallest + secondSmallest;
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

