  <h2><span class="tag">5·1</span> Occurrence of each element</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Sorted array of n integers — print how many times each element occurs. <b>Time O(n), Space O(1).</b></div>

    <h3>Key insight</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>In a sorted array, equal values are always adjacent — so compare <code class="i">ar[i]</code> with <code class="i">ar[i+1]</code>.</li>
      <li>Equal → same group → <code class="i">count++</code>. Not equal → group ended → print <code class="i">ar[i] + count</code>, then reset.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Three gotchas (all shown live)</h3>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li><code class="i">count</code> starts at <b>1</b> and resets to <b>1</b>, not 0 (else it lands one short).</li>
      <li>Loop to <code class="i">length-1</code> — <code class="i">ar[i+1]</code> at the last index throws <code class="i">ArrayIndexOutOfBounds</code>.</li>
      <li>The last group never hits an "else" — print it <b>after</b> the loop using <code class="i">ar[length-1]</code>.</li>
    </ol>

