<div class="part"><span>Day 9 · Rearrange Arrays</span></div>

<!-- 9.1 MOVE -1 TO FRONT -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">9·1</span> Move all −1 to the front</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Array has positives and <code class="i">-1</code>s. Push every <code class="i">-1</code> to the left, keep the positives in their <b>original relative order</b>. <b>No new array</b>, no sorting.</div>

    <h3>Two pointers, walking backward</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The <b>last</b> element stays put in the answer → start from the end.</li>
      <li><code class="i">i</code> <b>fetches</b>, <code class="i">j</code> <b>stores</b>. Both begin at <code class="i">length-1</code>.</li>
      <li><code class="i">ar[i] == -1</code> → skip it: only <code class="i">i--</code> (<code class="i">j</code> waits for a positive to land there).</li>
      <li>Else copy: <code class="i">ar[j--] = ar[i--]</code>.</li>
      <li>When <code class="i">i</code> falls below 0, everything from <code class="i">j</code> leftward is stale → fill it with <code class="i">-1</code>.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>RearrangeMinusOne.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">RearrangeMinusOne</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">rearrangeArray</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> i = ar.length - <span class="st">1</span>;
        <span class="ty">int</span> j = ar.length - <span class="st">1</span>;

        <span class="kw">while</span> (i &gt;= <span class="st">0</span>)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] == -<span class="st">1</span>)
            {
                i--;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span>
            {
                ar[j--] = ar[i--];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">while</span> (j &gt;= <span class="st">0</span>)
        {
            ar[j--] = -<span class="st">1</span>;
        }
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        rearrangeArray(ar);

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            System.out.print(ar[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
        }
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="run">
      <div class="rbar">▶ Run · RearrangeMinusOne</div>
      <div class="rbody">
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">10</div><div class="in">5 -1 3 -1 4 -1 5 3 8 2</div><div class="out">-1 -1 -1 5 3 4 5 3 8 2<span class="cmt">   // positives keep their order</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Why the caller sees the change</h3>
    <p>The method is <code class="i">void</code> and returns nothing, yet <code class="i">main</code> prints the rearranged array. An array is an <b>object</b> — passing <code class="i">ar</code> passes the <b>reference</b> (say address 3000), not a copy. Both <code class="i">ar</code> variables point to the same heap object, so edits inside the method are visible outside.</p>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- 9.2 MOVE ZEROS TO END -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">9·2</span> Move all zeros to the end</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Same idea, mirrored: push every <code class="i">0</code> to the right, keeping the non-zeros in order.</div>

    <h3>Flip the direction</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Now the <b>first</b> element stays put → traverse <b>forward</b>, both pointers from 0.</li>
      <li><code class="i">ar[i] == 0</code> → skip: only <code class="i">i++</code>. Else <code class="i">ar[j++] = ar[i++]</code>.</li>
      <li>After the loop, fill from <code class="i">j</code> to the end with <code class="i">0</code>.</li>
      <li>A <code class="i">for</code> loop works just as well as <code class="i">while</code> — same O(n).</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>RearrangeZeros.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">RearrangeZeros</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">rearrangeArray</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>;
        <span class="ty">int</span> j = <span class="st">0</span>;

        <span class="kw">while</span> (i &lt; ar.length)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i] == <span class="st">0</span>)
            {
                i++;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span>
            {
                ar[j++] = ar[i++];
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">while</span> (j &lt; ar.length)
        {
            ar[j++] = <span class="st">0</span>;
        }
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        rearrangeArray(ar);

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length; i++)
        {
            System.out.print(ar[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
        }
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="run">
      <div class="rbar">▶ Run · RearrangeZeros</div>
      <div class="rbody">
        <div class="rrun"><div class="in">8</div><div class="in">3 7 0 4 0 5 0 6</div><div class="out">3 7 4 5 6 0 0 0<span class="cmt">   // non-zeros keep their order</span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p style="color:var(--muted)">Pattern to remember: whichever side must stay fixed decides the traversal direction. Fetch pointer <code class="i">i</code> always moves; store pointer <code class="i">j</code> moves only when a keeper is copied. Then backfill the tail with the filler value.</p>

  </div>
</section>

