<!-- 10.1 PRINT CONSECUTIVE SUBARRAYS -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">10·1</span> Print all consecutive subarrays</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Print every run of consecutive numbers on its own line. <span class="arr">5 12 13 14 9 2 3 4 5 23</span> → <code class="i">5</code> / <code class="i">12 13 14</code> / <code class="i">9</code> / <code class="i">2 3 4 5</code> / <code class="i">23</code>.</div>

    <h3>Idea</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Two elements are consecutive when <code class="i">ar[i+1] - ar[i] == 1</code>.</li>
      <li>Consecutive → print <code class="i">ar[i]</code>, stay on the line. Not consecutive → print <code class="i">ar[i]</code>, then <b>newline</b> (the run just ended).</li>
      <li>Loop to <code class="i">length-1</code> (else <code class="i">ar[i+1]</code> overflows), then print the last element after the loop.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code">
