<!-- 10.4 LONGEST SUBARRAY -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">10·4</span> Print the longest consecutive subarray</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Print the elements of the longest run itself → <code class="i">2 3 4 5</code>.</div>

    <h3>The runner analogy</h3>
    <p>If a stopwatch says you ran <b>5 km</b> and the marker board reads <b>8 km</b>, where did you start? <code class="i">8 − 5 = 3</code>. Same here: knowing the <b>end index</b> and the <b>length</b> gives the start.</p>

    <h3>Idea</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Track <code class="i">ei</code> (end index) alongside <code class="i">max</code> — whenever <code class="i">max</code> updates inside the loop, set <code class="i">ei = i</code>. In the after-loop check, set <code class="i">ei = ar.length - 1</code> (<code class="i">i</code> isn't in scope).</li>
      <li>Then <code class="i">si = ei - max + 1</code> — the <b>+1</b> because both ends are inclusive.</li>
      <li>Print <code class="i">ar[si] … ar[ei]</code>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color:var(--muted)">Here: <code class="i">ei = 8</code>, <code class="i">max = 4</code> → <code class="i">si = 8 − 4 + 1 = 5</code> → indexes 5..8 = <code class="i">2 3 4 5</code>.</p>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>PrintLongestConsecutiveSubarray.java</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Scanner;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">PrintLongestConsecutiveSubarray</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">printLongestConsecutiveSubarray</span>(<span class="ty">int</span>[] ar)
    {
        <span class="ty">int</span> count = <span class="st">1</span>;
        <span class="ty">int</span> max = <span class="st">0</span>;
        <span class="ty">int</span> si = <span class="st">0</span>;
        <span class="ty">int</span> ei = <span class="st">0</span>;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length - <span class="st">1</span>; i++)
        {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i + <span class="st">1</span>] - ar[i] == <span class="st">1</span>)
            {
                count++;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span>
            {
                <span class="kw">if</span> (count &gt; max)
                {
                    max = count;
                    ei = i;
                }

                count = <span class="st">1</span>;
            }
        }

        <span class="kw">if</span> (count &gt; max)
        {
            max = count;
            ei = ar.length - <span class="st">1</span>;
        }

        si = ei - max + <span class="st">1</span>;

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = si; i &lt;= ei; i++)
        {
            System.out.print(ar[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
        }
    }

    <span class="kw">public static void</span> <span class="nm">main</span>(<span class="ty">String</span>[] args)
    {
        <span class="ty">Scanner</span> scan = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Scanner</span>(System.in);

        <span class="ty">int</span> n = scan.nextInt();
        <span class="ty">int</span>[] ar = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">int</span>[n];

        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; n; i++)
        {
            ar[i] = scan.nextInt();
        }

        printLongestConsecutiveSubarray(ar);
    }
}</code></pre>
    </div>

