<!-- 10.5 SORTED SUBARRAYS -->
<section class="prog">
  <h2><span class="tag">10·5</span> Sorted subarrays — one condition away</h2>
  <div class="body">

    <div class="q"><b>Q.</b> Print the sorted (non-decreasing) runs instead of the consecutive ones.</div>

    <h3>Only the condition changes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Consecutive: <code class="i">ar[i+1] - ar[i] == 1</code> &nbsp;→&nbsp; Sorted: <code class="i">ar[i+1] &gt; ar[i]</code></li>
      <li><b>Bug:</b> <code class="i">5 6 6 10</code> <i>is</i> sorted, but <code class="i">&gt;</code> breaks the run at the duplicate. Fix: <code class="i">ar[i+1] &gt;= ar[i]</code>.</li>
      <li>Descending sorted → <code class="i">ar[i+1] &lt;= ar[i]</code>.</li>
      <li>Everything else (length, max length, longest with si/ei) carries over unchanged.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="bar"><span>PrintSortedSubarrays.java (condition)</span><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
<pre><code class="block"><span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="ty">int</span> i = <span class="st">0</span>; i &lt; ar.length - <span class="st">1</span>; i++)
{
    <span class="kw">if</span> (ar[i + <span class="st">1</span>] &gt;= ar[i])          <span class="cm">// "&gt;" alone breaks on equal values</span>
    {
        System.out.print(ar[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
    }
    <span class="kw">else</span>
    {
        System.out.print(ar[i] + <span class="st">" "</span>);
        System.out.println();
